1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:05,158
When you start the activities, they will follow the same order as this lesson.

2
00:00:05,108 --> 00:00:10,815
First, you do a warm-up: Point to minimise, maximise and close.

3
00:00:10,815 --> 00:00:14,293
Explain that X means finished with this window.

4
00:00:14,293 --> 00:00:18,858
Then you answer quick checks, so we know the key words make sense.

5
00:00:18,858 --> 00:00:27,296
Next, you practise the real computer skill: Open one app, wait, minimise it, bring it back, then close it.

6
00:00:27,296 --> 00:00:28,858
Repeat slowly.

7
00:00:28,858 --> 00:00:35,394
You may also type a short answer, for example: Type the word for the button that closes a window.

8
00:00:35,394 --> 00:00:41,440
At the end, you finish with a stretch or reflection: Staff gives the four actions in order.

9
00:00:41,440 --> 00:00:44,470
You attempts each before staff prompts.

10
00:00:44,470 --> 00:00:47,021
Take one activity at a time.

11
00:00:47,021 --> 00:00:51,562
If you need help, ask staff, then try the next step yourself.

